Stay until the end, its so calming 🙏
.
𝗪𝗵𝗶𝗰𝗵 𝘀𝘁𝘆𝗹𝗲 𝗼𝗳 𝗺𝗲𝗱𝗶𝘁𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻 𝘀𝘂𝗶𝘁𝘀 𝘆𝗼𝘂 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗺𝗼𝘀𝘁? 👇
.
📽by @yukikawae 🌱
✒@anxiety_wellbeing 
.
Meditation is anything where you are able to be present with one thing and there are many different ways you can get a sense of meditation.
.
Regularly connecting with something that brings you into the present moment is a sign to your mind & body that you are safe & not in need of the stress response, anxiety.
.
Where as regularly connecting to things that cause stress, like fearful news, or constant distractions & info are signs of overwhelm.
.
Meditation
Here are some things that I connect with.

📚Reading takes me to a place in my mind I love the imagination 
🏖The beach sounds & visuals distract all other thoughts I am at peace
🕊Looking for and listening to nature connects me to life, I feel part of it.
🎵Music touches my heart strings, it can lift me high, can help me to connect to emotions inside to release them. I feel alive.
🌞Being in the sun and I start to drink it in, taking deep breaths. I feel energised.
⛈Thunder & rain connects me to our planet. I could listen for ages & wonder at the sights sounds.
.
There are many more visual, sounds, senses that give me that one focus and calms all others.
.
I saw this visual meditation video & thought you guys might enjoy.
.
𝗗𝗶𝗱 𝗶𝘁 𝗯𝗿𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘆𝗼𝘂 𝗰𝗮𝗹𝗺? 
.
For me I could watch this over & over i get calm from it. & it makes me want to try these actions, I think it would inspire calm.
.
Enjoy 🙏

🧘‍♀️Gentle yoga is a great action you can take to send signals to your mind & body of safety.
.
❤This helps to reinstate the parasympathetic nervous system, counteract the causes of anxiety, reduce the stress hormones, increase oxygen & release tension. Plus it's a nice thing to do, this gets you off your phone &  reconnecting to things that matter.
.
🧎‍♂️Many people find joy in this practice, so give it a try & let us know how you found it, everyone is different!
.
😊Check out @maracimatoribus she has some great videos for you to try, see what works for you!

.
👍Both myself & Priyanka @almaformula have collaborated to bring you this challenge & we will both be taking part.
.
🤔We will be consciously working on what we are in control of : behaviours such as 
.
Daily habits
Food choices
Thought Management
Morning rituals
Reconnecting to nature
etc.

All these will impact our thoughts & feelings.
Reduce fear
Reduce anxiety
Boost wellbeing & immunity.
Win Win Win!
.
👉Each weekend we will go live for a Q & A. After the live, we will be posting up what you need, to be prepared for the week. (things you may already have or are very affordable to get) So that you don't arrive at one day and think "I am not ready" & then decide you can't join in. 
.
👉Each evening between 9pm French time we will be posting up what to do for the following day.
So that you know what to expect, as some of the activities are designed to be, as you wake up.
.
👉You can follow myself & @almaformula we will be doing the challenge ourselves & documenting this in our stories to give you two different perspectives from the challenge as well as your own. 
.
👉There will be links given as we go, for ideas, downloadables etc. as part of the challenge. 
.
👉If you are thinking you can't do this, it may be too long?
.
👉HERE'S a Helpful perception
Life sometimes happens, even myself, I may have a day when it's not possible to achieve that days activity, like too many urgent things may take over. That's fine & not a reason to beat myself up or decide I've failed, feel bad & the choose to not take part the next day. No i'll take the day I need & will be ready the next day.
.
👉Also this is a challenge to be taken with interest & discovery of self. To become aware of what behaviours we choose that may influence our thoughts & feelings. Not to tell ourselves off, but to know where we can make the first step.
.
👉We are in control of our behaviours & this will impact/influence on our though & feelings.
.
👉Up next is the shopping list.
👉Sunday 9pm gmt +1 Monday's challenge Will be posted.
👉Monday websites & links to what you need.
👉Everything will be saved in the highlights & IGTV for you to try at any time.
.

👍Join us on Monday the 19th of october. Both myself & Priyanka @almaformula have collaborated to bring you this challenge & we will both be taking part.
.
🤔We will be consciously working on what we are in control of : behaviours such as 
.
Daily habits
Food choices
Thought Management
Morning rituals
Reconnecting to nature
etc.

All these will impact our thoughts & feelings.
Reduce fear
Reduce anxiety
Boost wellbeing & immunity.
Win Win Win!
.
👉Each Saturday we will go live for a Q & A. After the live, we will be posting up what you need, to be prepared for the week. (things you may already have or are very affordable to get) So that you don't arrive at one day and think "I am not ready" & then decide you can't join in. 
.
👉Each evening between 9pm French time we will be posting up what to do for the following day.
So that you know what to expect, as some of the activities are designed to be, as you wake up.
.
👉You can follow myself & @almaformula we will be doing the challenge ourselves & documenting this in our stories to give you two different perspectives from the challenge as well as your own. 
.
👉There will be links given as we go, for ideas, downloadables etc. as part of the challenge. 
.
👉If you are thinking you can't do this, it may be too long?
.
👉HERE'S a Helpful perception
Life sometimes happens, even myself, I may have a day when it's not possible to achieve that days activity, like too many urgent things may take over. That's fine & not a reason to beat myself up or decide I've failed, feel bad & the choose to not take part the next day. No i'll take the day I need & will be ready the next day.
.
👉Also this is a challenge to be taken with interest & discovery of self. To become aware of what behaviours we choose that may influence our thoughts & feelings. Not to tell ourselves off, but to know where we can make the first step.
.
👉We are in control of our behaviours & this will impact/influence on our though & feelings.
.
👉Up next is the shopping list.
👉Sunday 9pm gmt +1 Monday's challenge Will be posted.
👉Monday websites & links to what you need.
👉Everything will be saved in the highlights & IGTV for you to try at any time.
.
😊

node.text:
𝗧𝗶𝗿𝗲𝗱 of trying to make lemonade? Maybe we could ignore some of the 🍋's?
.
🎨@will_santino_illustration
✒@anxiety_wellbeing 
.
🍋IGNORE THE lemons? What do you mean?
.
Let me take you back 20+ years ago. 
I had a panic response on an underground train that after, although shook up I didn't have any long term issues. Then I had another one in a shopping mall, ran to the bus, ran home & from there i was panicking every 30 minutes for 6 months.
Everything was scary! Caused more panic.
There was not 1 second in the day of calm.
I felt like I was in a storm of lemons, couldn't see my was out. Gradually feeling like there were tons of them on me!
.
To cut a long story short, I became afraid of what i would do if nothing changed. I saw a doc, a cbt therapist, learnt about anxiety, what was happening, why I was responding, went back to school learnt about the brain, nutrition, psychology etc for more info on the causes.
20+ years later I am a cbt practitioner, holistic anxiety coach. 
.
But what did I learn that was the best piece of info to come out of all that?
.
Not every🍋is true.

I beleived because of that one panic response that everything coming my way after that was a 🍋(fear)& for my full attention. That I was helpless.(I wasn't)This caused more fear & caused more panic, then I was only responding😱
.
Sometimes lemons can be
.
🍋False Evidence Appearing Real
🍋Fearful Outside influence 
.
Example of outside🍋's
Right now the media are throwing these things at us everyday, causing fear, we are trying to survive, but look at the ones in charge are they doing that?
.
Could it be that alot of this info is hearsay, maybes, might's, pressumued, estimated, worst case scenario, feared to be? Etc 
.
In my control👇
.
🍋I was believing I was in constant danger but I wasn't. I had to start saying that although I feel scared I am safe. Although I think something bad might happen, will it? Ask questions get interested instead of scared.
.
A belief, thought, feeling can be untrue.
.
You can
Before you react 
Try not to believe the 1st meaning
Pay attention to the wording
Switch off
Distract
.
Work on you. Outside is only in your influence not your control. 
.
#anxiety

node.text:
You know what you need 𝗯𝘂𝘁, a doubtful thought takes your attention & then what?
Why do we get this type of thought? What should you do?
.
🎨@silviadoesdrawings
✒@anxiety_wellbeing 

Then what? 
Well you'll already be tired & in need but now you might start to feel down & anxious. Because any fearful thoughts like👇cause anxiety

I need to but👇
💭What if someone judges me 
💭What if they think Im lazy
💭I can't, must not
.
💭So now Im stuck, I have to feel this way or be afraid, which is worse?
.
💭How will I continue my day?
.
💭I'll be like this forever its helpless
.
Then before you know it these thoughts are enough to signal danger & panic.
All this on top of your needs 
.
❤
.
We get these types of thoughts from our past & present experiences.

Did anyone say you were lazy before? Or say something that you thought meant the same thing? 
Did anyone act as thought taking a break was wrong?
Have you percieved things to be, not good at all if you're not constantly showing you are being productive?
How do you view society? Feel like working harder?
 
This is where the influence of your beliefs, ideas, thoughts comes from but is it true? Or do you just think it is because of what you have experienced before?
.
It is normal for your mind to remember past events & equate them to be the meaning for the future. The minds job is to find meaning for everything & protect you.
 
So if you've learnt 
Better not👇
Upset anyone by looking lazy
Because someone will judge me
Take a break they will tell me off 
Better have a reason for relaxing
Etc
.
Then relaxing everyday, & not just when you need it or relaxing at all will feel like a tug of war. Its normal considering all these experiences from the past.
.
The good news is the past doesn't=the future & beliefs, ideas, thoughts change because we can influence the meaning, by influencing our perception.
.
Things to tell yourself
If I need a break I do.
I dont need to justify my meaning.
If today its not possible then this weekend I am cancelling plans because I need it.
I will say I need a break or I will breakdown. #human being over here.
Its not my job to change what my taking a break means to them.
I need it.
.
#anxiety

node.text:
Humans are 𝗺𝗲𝗮𝗻𝗶𝗻𝗴 making beings, we need to know why? So you are normal to what if. Why? 👇
.
🎨@crazyheadcomics 
✒@anxiety_wellbeing 
.
👉Why do we need to know why? 
.
Because, we are actually animals that called themselves the human race but ultimately we are born & our job is to survive & create the next generation in order for our species to continue. So our minds job is to protect us & to survive any potential danger. 
.
Makes sense that you try not to put your hand back into a fire. That you may run when faced with a danger or fight or freeze depending on the situation & which response suited best.
.
Our body & mind work as a team, the mind wants to protect us too & needs to know what things mean, in order to know if were safe or not. How else will you have an idea if you're safe or not but by through your senses & perceptions.
.
Which is why we search for meaning 
.
What did you mean when you said or did that? 
Did you mean something bad about me?
What if something bad was to happen?
.
These thoughts are normal but they are not facts & those thoughts come from our perceptions but perceptions can change.
.
So if you find yourself what iffing the worst, try to step in with some balance.
.
'I know my mind is protecting me but it doesn't mean its perception is correct. What if it went very well? Ah didn't think about that. Yes thats a possibility too. Plus what we believe might happen will effect our thoughts, feelings & behaviours which will=the outcome 
.
Example 
Perception: What if I fail?
Thought: you will look silly
Feel: Worried, anxious 
Behaviours : avoid this
Outcome : never know what they are capable of.
.
You can intercept a normal thought with some acceptance & a question.
.
Ok but what if i learn lots?
Thought : I could gain more confidence in this subject?
Feel : Optimistic, interested
Behaviours : look for more info, join in.
Outcome : Starts experiencing something new, realises new is a good thing, an opportunity. That thay are capable.
.
Try not to beat yourself up for thoughts, they are all normal but which ones are you going to repeat to yourself? Helpful ones or limited.
You get to choose. 
.
#anxiety #anxietycoach #anxietyhelp
